        <div type="translation">
            <ab>[Translation from P. L. Bat. 19. 42:]

          Written in year 14, third month of the pr.t-season, day 16 (= 16 Phamenoth). The one who speaks to Totoês, son of Imuthês, the Overseer of the Mystery of Osorbuchis:
          "perform burial for Hatrês, son of Lamenthis",
          is the scribe Pelaias, son of Pamenôs the elder, the priest who enters, of the first phyle.

          [Translation from Short Texts 2. 426, with corrections:]

          Written in year 14, 3rd month of the šmw season (Epeiph), day 6. The one who says before Tutu, son of Imhotep, &lt;the&gt; overseer of the mystery of Osorbuchis, 
          'Perform buial for Hatre, son of Lamenth(is),'
          is scribe Pelaiha, son of Pamenh the elder, the priest who enters, of the first phyle.</ab>
        </div>
